TY  - JOUR
AU  - Eriksen, Kristoffer W.
AU  - Kvaløy, Ola
T1  - Myopic Investment Management*
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfp019
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 14
IS  - 3
SP  - 521
EP  - 542
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Myopic loss aversion (MLA) has been proposed as an explanation for the equity premium puzzle, and experiments indicate that investors exhibit behavior consistent with MLA. But a caveat is that a large bulk of financial assets is managed by investment managers whose objectives may differ substantially from those of private investors. Most importantly they manage their clients' money, not their own. In this paper we test experimentally how individuals take risk with other people's (“clients”) money. We find that subjects behave consistently with MLA over their clients' money and take less risk with their clients' money than with their own.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfp019
ER  - 



